    "Furthermore, IoT-based predictive maintenance at John Deere has decreased equipment downtime by 50%, resulting in a 20% reduction in operational waste.",
    "By incorporating such data, readers can gain a clear and quantifiable understanding of the significant benefits that IoT brings to agriculture (FAO 2002).",
    "IoT applications in agriculture, such as smart greenhouse systems, soil moisture sensors, and automation of farming machinery, have resulted in improved efficiency, reduced production costs, increased product quality, and enhanced sustainability (Babakhouya et al. 2023; Cihan 2023).",
    "By utilizing IoT devices like sensors to collect soil parameters and implementing Machine Learning models to recommend suitable crops, farmers can achieve higher yields and profits.",
    "Additionally, IoT-enabled solutions in agriculture have led to a 1.75% increase in crop yield, a 13% decrease in energy costs per acre, and an 8% reduction in water use for irrigation (Babakhouya et al. 2023; Singh et al. 2023a, b)."
